                                                          </div>
                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="line-height:normal;margin-bottom:12.0pt;"><a href="https://www.patrickautreaux.fr/en/"><strong>Patrick Autréaux</strong></a>&nbsp;(b. 1968) is the author of dozens of books, mainly published by Gallimard and Verdier, and articles in French in <em>Europe</em>, <em>Esprit</em>, <em>NRF</em>, etc. His novel In the <em>Valley of Tears</em> was published by UIT Books in 2019. His essays appear in <em>Socrates on the Beach</em>, <em>Asymptote</em>, <em>3:am</em> magazine, Sublunary Editions, Black Herald Press, and AGNI. Recently, <em>Pussyboy</em> (Verdier), a novel about an erotic passion, was translated into Spanish. He has been a fellow at the Dora Maar House (Nancy Brown Negley Foundation), at Passa Porta (Belgium), and has been writer-in-residence at Boston University and MIT. His new novel,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gallimard.fr/catalogue/l-epoux/9782073090324"><em>L’Époux</em></a>, was released by Gallimard in 2025.</p>
                                            <div class="clear"></div>
                                                          
                                                                                                                                        <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="line-height:normal;margin-bottom:12.0pt;"><strong>Tobias Ryan</strong> is a translator from Wales, UK, currently based in Paris, France. His writing and translations have appeared in <em>Firmament</em> magazine, <em>Berfrois</em>, <em>Hyperion</em> magazine and elsewhere. He is co-editor-in-chief of&nbsp;<a href="https://minorliteratures.com/"><em>Minor Literature[s]</em></a>.</p>
